uri et al. 2000) which are believed to be in the latter\nstages of merging. This result implies that the cores of superclusters are\nenvironments where radio emission, particularly resultant from AGN, is\nsuppressed in the later stages of merging. Thus, radio observations of clusters\nmight be sensitive indicators of the precise merger stage of the cluster but\nmore observational evidence is still required to establish this trend.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 29 Jul 2008 06:03:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
