 except for $w$, for which the uncertainty is twice as\nlarge. At the same time, this possible evolution is severely constrained. We\nconclude that systematic uncertainties for some estimated quantities are\nsimilar or larger than statistical ones.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 29 Jul 2008 09:14:37 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 9 Mar 2009 18:05:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-13"}
